msgid "Sorry."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid "It's my first time."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid "No, not my first time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (15f)
#. 3: pause (30f)
msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see.<2.pa>\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"These plains are home to many quality\n"
"horses. In the past, nomadic tribes would\n"
"gather here, but...<3.pa>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I can only hope that someone steps up\n"
"and deals with those hooligans...<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid "<1.so>You took care of the<2.se_co> hooligans<3.re_co>?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Horses really love it! Try sharing it with\n"
"one, and you'll see what I mean!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (30f)
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Nowadays, <2.se_co>bands of riders <3.re_co>roam the\n"
"plains, acting like they own the place.<4.pa>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, really? I'm so glad to hear that.\n"
"I'm counting on you!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid "<1.so>Oh. Well, sorry for bothering you..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid "<1.so>Is this your first time here?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (30f)
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm counting on you...<2.pa>\n"
"But don't overdo it, OK?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid "<1.so>This is a small token of my thanks!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (30f)
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I want to give you something...<2.pa>\n"
"but your inventory seems to be full.\n"
"Come back later, OK?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (15f)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I saw you.<2.pa> You took care of those jerks\n"
"that thought they owned the plain.\n"
"We were all fed up with them."
msgstr ""

